##Dictated by Dr. Oxford, desperate to "move" equipment to support the production of nucleic acid kits

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Under the epidemic, to see so many medical workers and scientists working day and night, just to fight the epidemic, as a young scientist, I want to contribute to my country, to the world within the scope of my discipline.

Dictation | Fan Mengzhen

Finishing | Huang Yinglin

On February 25,2020, at 6:00 pm, that is, 10:00 am UK time, my domestic partner called and said, "the equipment has been delivered to the lab and the preliminary installation has been completed! " I was relieved after several days of suspense, the good news made Oxford's recent overcast days less depressing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The automatic liquid-moving equipment donated by me was received by a biotechnology company in Shanghai

My name is Fan Mengzhen, and I am a fourth year phd student in Chemistry at University of Oxford. Since the outbreak of the new crown disease, I have been watching the domestic epidemic trends, the new crown pneumonia (COVID-19) rapid nucleic acid detection and diagnosis of the topic quickly attracted my attention. Because my doctoral research focuses on gene sequencing and cancer diagnosis, nucleic acid testing fits well with my field of study. At the beginning of the epidemic, how to diagnose NCP became a big problem, and nucleic acid detection based on real-time polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) became an important diagnostic method. This is my area of expertise, I think my expertise can help, so I immediately contact a few domestic rapid nucleic acid test kit production units, and they exchanged gene sequencing and chemical synthesis experience. In the course of communicating with them, I learned that as the number of suspected cases increased, the pressure to produce the kits became more and more obvious. As a young scientist myself, I know that the production of kits involves complex chemical reagent and biological sample injection and transfer operations, so automated equipment is very important for kit production. In such an emergency situation, it is very difficult for reagent box manufacturers to procure high-quality equipment in a short period of time.

Ot-2 automatic transfer station made in USA

Then I remembered that in 2019, when my high school Alma Mater, No. 2 High School of East China Normal University, was celebrating its 60th anniversary, I had donated an OT-2 automatic mobile workstation made in the United States to the school in the hope of supporting educational activities. Industry 4.0 is an automated scientific research facility with a robotic arm and a specially designed high throughput pipette gun that can perform automated pipette operations instead of human hands. The manipulator moves fluid much faster than the human hand, and the highly standardized mechanical operation greatly reduces the possibility of human error. The equipment can be operated at full capacity 24 hours as long as the raw material supply is sufficient. The pipette is nearly 100 times more efficient than conventional equipment. Therefore, the precision, accuracy, efficiency and reliability of this scientific research equipment are much better than those of the general production equipment in the production of medical products. Therefore, I think that if the existing scientific research equipment to the reagent box production units, may be able to solve the immediate problem.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
No. 2 High School of East China Normal University teachers quickly packed up the equipment

With that in mind, I immediately contacted my high school alma mater to express my desire to donate equipment to a kit manufacturer. My request was immediately given the full support of the school. With the consent of the school, I began to work with partners on the National Health Commission designated nucleic acid test kit production units. After consulting the experts, we decided to donate the equipment to a biotechnology company in Shanghai after considering the factors of production capacity, staffing and transportation of special equipment. At the same time, No. 2 High School of East China Normal University leaders and teachers got to work immediately and, despite the winter break, returned to the school to pack up their equipment, completing the urgent repacking on Feb. 18,2020. The equipment is delivered to the kit production unit by a professional logistics company to support the production of anti-epidemic diagnostic products including nucleic acid test kits after successful commissioning.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I used Weibo@fan's science to spread knowledge about the prevention of new coronary pneumonia

In addition to donations, when I watch the news, I often observe that many people wear masks in the wrong way, and can not play an effective protective role. Especially for the N95 mask, which is rarely used in normal times, some users have not mastered the correct wearing method. As a young scientist, I feel it is my duty to inform you about the prevention of new crown pneumonia (COVID-19) . So, I started to shoot some popular science videos myself and post them on Weibo to teach people to wear masks. At the same time also through the short video popular science to you different types of masks and protective index, I hope you use reasonably, do not waste precious medical resources.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I had airlifted the anti-epidemic supplies from England to Guangzhou, and my little friend was packing them up for shipment to all parts of Hubei

As the epidemic spread across Europe, there was also a sense of panic and a shortage of face masks in the UK. I had bought some masks to send home. In fact, at the beginning of the outbreak, I began collecting supplies in the UK and donated 24 batches of medical supplies to 11 provinces and cities, including Hubei, Shanghai, Beijing, Xinjiang, Inner Mongolia and Guangxi. Now, the Oxford University campus began to organize free distribution of masks to alleviate the anxiety of teachers and students.
